arStrings.szText: We must find Yorin as quickly as possible. I realize how hopeless this all seems, but I've spent half my life studying the soulstone. I know its nature.
In denial. Trying to "logic" his way out of this hopeless situation. Flustered.
It will take time for Astaroth to overpower my boy. I taught him well. Even now, he is resisting the demon’s influence.
In denial. Trying to "logic" his way out of this hopeless situation. Flustered.
They'll be close by. Cerrigar, perhaps. All those innocents to burn will excite Astaroth...make him fight harder to...to take control...

A touch more urgency here as he forms a "plan" in the first two sentences. Trailing off for the last sentence as he thinks about the implications of this--Astaroth will overpower and transform his son.
Lilith has what she wanted from Astaroth. Why would she linger here?
